## 13. SECURITY

- **Never trust user input.** Validate and sanitize everything before use.
- **SQL injection**: parameterized queries always, forever. No exceptions.
- **Authentication**: validate JWTs in middleware — use a well-maintained library (`golang-jwt/jwt`). Never roll your own crypto.
- **Secrets in environment**: never commit secrets to source control. Use secret managers (Vault, AWS Secrets Manager) in production.
- **TLS**: all inter-service communication must use TLS. Let the platform handle termination (load balancer / service mesh).
- **Rate limiting**: every public endpoint. Per-IP by default, per-user for authenticated endpoints.
- **Input size limits**: set `http.MaxBytesReader` on all request bodies.
- **CORS**: allowlist specific origins — never `*` in production for authenticated APIs.
- **Dependency auditing**: run `govulncheck` and `go mod tidy` in CI. Pin dependencies.
- **Principle of least privilege**: database users have only the permissions they need. No superuser connections from app code.

