## 14. DEPENDENCY MANAGEMENT

```
go.mod   — defines module path and Go version
go.sum   — checksums for reproducible builds
```

### Rules

- Keep `go.mod` clean. Run `go mod tidy` before every commit.
- Vendor (`go mod vendor`) for air-gapped or reproducibility-critical builds.
- Prefer standard library. Add a dependency only when the cost of writing it yourself outweighs the cost of a dependency.
- Before adding a dependency: check stars, last commit date, open issues, license, and API stability.
- Avoid indirect dependencies with security histories. Run `govulncheck ./...` in CI.
- Pin major versions. Never use `replace` directives in production modules.

### Approved Dependency Categories

| Category | Preferred library |
|---|---|
| HTTP router | `chi`, `gorilla/mux`, or stdlib `net/http` |
| SQL | `database/sql` + `lib/pq` or `jackc/pgx` |
| Config | `kelseyhightower/envconfig` or `caarlos0/env` |
| Logging | `log/slog` (stdlib) or `rs/zerolog` |
| Testing | `testify/assert`, `testify/mock` |
| UUIDs | `google/uuid` |
| Migrations | `golang-migrate/migrate` |
| Errors | `stdlib errors` + `fmt.Errorf("%w")` |
| Observability | `prometheus/client_golang`, `open-telemetry/opentelemetry-go` |

