## 15. CI/CD & MAKEFILE

Every repo must have a `Makefile` as the single interface for common operations:

```makefile
.PHONY: build test lint vet fmt run migrate

build:
	go build -o bin/myservice ./cmd/myservice

test:
	go test ./... -race -count=1 -timeout=60s

test/integration:
	go test ./... -tags=integration -race -count=1 -timeout=120s

lint:
	golangci-lint run ./...

vet:
	go vet ./...

fmt:
	gofmt -w .
	goimports -w .

run:
	go run ./cmd/myservice

migrate/up:
	migrate -path ./migrations -database $$DATABASE_URL up

migrate/down:
	migrate -path ./migrations -database $$DATABASE_URL down 1
```

### CI Pipeline (required steps)

1. `go vet ./...`
2. `golangci-lint run`
3. `go test ./... -race -count=1`
4. `govulncheck ./...`
5. `docker build` (verify image builds)

### Linter Config (`golangci-lint`)

Enable at minimum: `errcheck`, `gosimple`, `govet`, `ineffassign`, `staticcheck`, `unused`, `revive`, `gofmt`, `goimports`.

